Creating View in SQL Server 2

·        View is a virtual table in SQL server

·         Though, it is a Table it is not stored in Database like other tables

·         It will be stored as SQL Objects so occupying memory space will be less

·         Inside the View, we used Complex SQL Query with a Select Statement we also used Joins with in the
 select statement for joining the  7 tables.

·         Inside the Select statement we used Case Statement to Clean the Data(To change Null values to Meaningful value)

·         Double Click or Right Click on the file that you Downloaded ---- > Open


·         It will open in SSMS (SQL Server Management Studio) . Click Execute


·         File executed Successfully


·         Right Click on Views under ColaberryDatabase ----- > Refresh


·         Click on ‘+’ icon of Views, there will be the View that we created.
